            TN( t1 ,
    
                "<CENTER>\r\n"
                "<TABLE style=\"width: 80%\">\r\n"
                    "<TR>\r\n"
                        "<TD colspan=2 align=center valign=top style=\"\">"
                            "<iframe width=\"425\" height=\"350\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" marginheight=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" src=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=2620+19th+Ave,+san+francisco&amp;sll=37.0625,-95.677068&amp;sspn=81.04919,108.984375&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;ll=37.74934,-122.471209&amp;spn=0.0103,0.013304&amp;z=14&amp;iwloc=addr&amp;output=embed&amp;s=AARTsJr3zAB60d-ZoOtI1DR9R1ZCFwiACA\"></iframe><br /><small><a href=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=2620+19th+Ave,+san+francisco&amp;sll=37.0625,-95.677068&amp;sspn=81.04919,108.984375&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;ll=37.74934,-122.471209&amp;spn=0.0103,0.013304&amp;z=14&amp;iwloc=addr&amp;source=embed\" style=\"color:" ifcCOLORhTMLwHAT_BACKnORMAL "0FF;text-align:left\">View Larger Map</a></small>\r\n"
                        "</TD>\r\n"
                    "</TR>\r\n"
                    "<TR>\r\n"
                        "<TD align=center valign=top style=\"\">"
                            "<IMG SRC=\"/blob/nautilus.gif\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\">\r\n"
                        "</TD>\r\n"
                        "<TD align=center valign=top style=\"\">"
                            "<IMG SRC=\"/blob/organizer.gif\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\">\r\n"
                        "</TD>\r\n"
                    "</TR>\r\n"
                "</TABLE>\r\n"
                "</CENTER>\r\n"
                "<P>\r\n"
                "Four hours ago, at 8 AM (July 13, 2008), I was staring down the barrel of a semiautomatic handgun.\r\n"
                "  Slowly, after a syrupy long moment where I \"saw\" my mind comprehend the reality of the gun in my face, I acknowledged what the officer was saying and began to narrate each movement that my hands were about to make to comply, moving my hands slowly and smoothly.\r\n"
                "  That barrel was 6 inches from my forehead for a very, very long time.\r\n"
                "  As I responded, my mind took note of the new, unused appearance of the shiny black gun, of the details and even artfulness of its design, and of the large bore of its barrel.\r\n"
                "  Somehow, I knew exactly what to say and what to do, and there was a complete calm, as though nothing unusual was occuring.\r\n"
                "<P>\r\n"
                "Have you ever wondered how you would react to a gun in your face?\r\n"
                "  I have.\r\n"
                "  And now I know!\r\n"
                "<P>\r\n"
                "For 30 years, as I have careened through adult life, I have occasionally wondered what the hell it was that I learned at the University of Chicago, and whether I would ever reap any profit from those hellish years.\r\n"
                "  I now comprehend the essence of that education.\r\n"
                "  As I passed through that pressure cooker, do or die (figuratively) graduate program in economics, my mind was trained to make urgent high stakes decisions instantly, instinctively, and correctly.\r\n"
                "  Henceforth, I shall walk with a new awareness of the lethality of the law enforcement officers with whom I must interact.\r\n"
                "  I will also walk with a new awareness of what I became in, how I was formed by, the economics graduate program at the University of Chicago.\r\n"
                "<P>\r\n"
                "I want the following little snippet of my life as a civic and political activist to rouse you to action.\r\n"
                "  Not the whole of you; just one of your fingers.\r\n"
                "  IdeaFarm " "(tm) Operations consumes the whole of me; it is my passion.\r\n"
                "  But those who join me will never be asked to do more than \"lift a finger\".\r\n"
                "<P>\r\n"
                "I am weary of the many people who wish me luck and say now nice it is that I am on the streets with signs encouraging people to live unselfishly.\r\n"
                "  Free speech work in the United States today is very difficult, and very dangerous.\r\n"
                "  People don't listen.\r\n"
                "  Those who listen smile, but are not moved to act.\r\n"
                "  And I face very real mortal danger every single day of my life, as I work to rouse the people of the United States from the coma of \"thought steering\".\r\n"
                "<P>\r\n"
                "My vehicle, an old Dodge Caravan, has a 16' by 16' sign on each side, a 4' by 8' sign in the rear, and a 2' by 4' sign in the front.\r\n"
                "  There is a platform on top, 12' above the pavement.\r\n"
                "  Every night, I park it on a busy boulevard somewhere in the San Francisco Bay area.\r\n"
                "  For security as well as lifestyle choice reasons, I sleep in the vehicle.\r\n"
                "  My speech activity would be impossible if I did not do that.\r\n"
                "  Like everyone else, I must work to obtain money.\r\n"
                "  But I manage to display these signs in all of the cities in the South Bay, as well as in San Francisco, Oakland, and Hayward, on a regular schedule.\r\n"
                "  In addition, I display them in other communities within my reach from my central operations location in the South Bay.\r\n"
                "<P>\r\n"
                "  Sleeping in my vehicle is not an offense against the people of the State of California.\r\n"
                "  It is a necessary fundamental act of living that cannot be avoided while prosecuting my civic and political speech activity.\r\n"
                "  Because I am present, I have lawfully repelled many unlawful interferences with this speech activity by law enforcement officers.\r\n"
                "  Had I not been present, those officers would have deluged me with citations of various kinds, as well as unlawful tow aways of the vehicle.\r\n"
                "  I have also repelled three vandals, one of which broke a window, another of which began to break in, and a third stole something fastened to the roof.\r\n"
                "  This does not include the gang of men in South Oakland who began to demolish the signage late at night while I was inside, not daring to make a noise.\r\n"
                "  Those men were repelled by some civic minded apartment dweller, who called the police and yelled at them.\r\n"
                "  The vehicle has been egged thoroughly several times by mischievous teenagers, and it has been paint balled.\r\n"
                "  Threats to my person and my vehicle have come to me directly as well as passed along to me by citizens who overheard someone speak of malicious intent.\r\n"
                "<P>\r\n"
                "One humorous memory that I treasure is of a group of young men walking toward the Nautilus (my vehicle) around midnight in the Tenderloin district of San Francisco.\r\n"
                "  This memory is several years old, dating back to earlier signage that read, \"The root problem is that you have become a selfish people.\"\r\n"
                "  As I lay going to sleep, I heard the footsteps approaching close by, and then I heard one of the youths say, \"No, don't!  That's a <I>holy vehicle</I>.\"\r\n"
                "  Another memory, humorous for a different reason, is of a youth in Castro Valley who, approaching the vehicle around noon, read a portion of the current signage aloud in a very snotty, disrespectful voice intended to mimic me, \"Come, Eat With Us!\".\r\n"
                "  Then he added, in his own, very angry and hostile voice, \"Fuck You!\".\r\n"
                "  More pleasantly, three teenagers (three occasions), while passing the Nautilus on their bicycles, have proclaimed in a loud, civic minded, assertive voice, \"Fuck selfish people!\"\r\n"
                "  (One of them used slightly less crude language.)\r\n"
                "  Finally, in Mountain View, a group of about 10 high school students approached the Nautilus while crossing Castro Street.\r\n"
                "  One of them read the signage aloud to his fellow students, \"Make Life Better!\" and then proclaimed, \"IdeaFarm " "(tm) rocks.\"\r\n"
                "  I would have none of these wonderful memories if the Nautilus was not my home.\r\n"
                "<P>\r\n"
                "  All three windows on the passenger side are broken out.\r\n"
                "  I broke the rear window while trying to gain entrance after locking my keys inside.\r\n"
                "  The middle window was broken by a sheriff of San Mateo County during a standoff on Highway 84.\r\n"
                "  The front window was broken in Hayward by a vandal who shattered it onto my lap while I was brushing my teeth!\r\n"
                "  Given my chosen method of civic and political speech, sleeping in my car is required so that I can answer challenges and inquiries from law enforcement officers, so that I can repel vandals, so that I can repel unlawful police actions, so that I can make myself accountable for safety / road hazard issues, and so that I can display the signs throughout the Bay Area.\r\n"
                "<P>\r\n"
                "You might say that I should use another method to disseminate my message.\r\n"
                "  But the law of this land is clear on the point: the speaker has the right to choose the method, and the people cannot foreclose a general method of speech.\r\n"
                "  My method is very effective and has relatively low nuisance costs to the community.\r\n"
                "  My choice of methods is restricted because my message is mortally hostile to the \"thought steering\" media, which is funded by advertising and inevitabley caters to the interests of advertisers.\r\n"
                "  Power is concentrated in the media industry, and it became more concentrated during my lifetime.\r\n"
                "  The media industry cannot be trusted with the message, \"Don't Be Selfish!\".\r\n"
                "  It also cannot be trusted with the message, \"This society is awash in a very powerful, overwhelming form of \"thought steering\".\r\n"
                "  My civic and political speech must be disseminated using a method that is independent of the powers of the media industry.\r\n"
                "  It also must be accessible to a poor man, because I am a poor man, up to my ears in credit card debt, with a very low and very unreliable income as a temporary worker.\r\n"
                "<P>\r\n"
                "My civic and political speech activity, using signs on a car that I relocate throughout a region and sleep in, is a test of our \"emergency civil rights system\".\r\n"
                "  Can a poor man with a message that is hostile to the media but has widespread public appeal and acceptance get his message out?\r\n"
                "  Will he be heard in the San Francisco Bay Area?\r\n"
                "  Will his words have meaningful effect, rather than just produce smiles and nods and well wishes?\r\n"
                "  That question is the real significance of my crusade, my war against selfishness.\r\n"
                "<P>\r\n"
                "The answer is in your hands, and in the hands of the armed law enforcement officers who interfere with my civic and political speech activities.\r\n"
                "<P>\r\n"
                "What, you ask, did I do to get the handgun in my face?\r\n"
                "  I slept in a bit, snoozed and woke up unhurriedly, and finally arose from a great night's sleep around 7:45 AM.\r\n"
                "  Just as I was about to roll up my sleeping bag and let the air out of my mattress, I heard someone manipulating the signs on the Nautilus roughly.\r\n"
                "  Thinking that it was some vandal, I froze and kept quiet.\r\n"
                "  When I heard a two way radio crackle, I said loudly, \"Are you law enforcement?\"\r\n"
                "  The police responded, \"Come out of the vehicle.\"\r\n"
                "  \"Damn!\", I thought.\r\n"
                "  I was still in my pajamas and there was no way to get the sleeping bag and mattress stowed out of sight.\r\n"
                "<P>\r\n"
                "Resigned to a hassle about sleeping in my vehicle, I said, \"I am going to take away the blind over the passenger side window.\"\r\n"
                "  The window isn't glass; that was broken out by the vandal in Hayward.\r\n"
                "  I replaced it with a vinyl screen, which has many advantages, one of which is the ability to converse with law enforcement officers without unlocking and opening the door.\r\n"
                "  After setting down the blinder, I placed both of my hands onto the sill below the window screen, so that they would be in the plain view of the officer.\r\n"
                "  I always do that, out of habit, because it's usually 1 AM and the officers outside have no idea whether I am dangerous or not.\r\n"
                "  The officer repeated, \"Come out of the vehicle.\"\r\n"
                "  Knowing that it is lawful to obstruct an officer if, and only if, he has no authority in law to give a particular order, I asked, \"By what authority do you demand this?\"\r\n"
                "  He must have had his gun behind him, because in less than a blink of an eye, that gun was in my face, with his partner standing behind him, ready to riddle the Nautilus with lead.\r\n"
                "<P>\r\n"
                "Under stress and danger, when there is no time to think, you do what prior experience has trained you to do.\r\n"
                "  The law says that a police officer may not tow away a homeless person's vehicle.\r\n"
                "  But the law also says that the vehicle can be towed if it is creating a hazard.\r\n"
                "  Police officers view the latter provision as a blank check enabling them to confiscate a man's home without warning at 1 AM.\r\n"
                "  Police have threatened to do this numerous times, forcing me to wake up and drive to a different city.\r\n"
                "  Several years ago, in Milpitas, in a situation nearly identical to that of this story, I got out of the vehicle and ended up arrested with my vehicle towed away.\r\n"
                "  Since then, I have learned to never get out of the vehicle as long as there is some legal justification for staying within.\r\n"
                "  The no sleeping in vehicle laws are patently unconstitutional, so when that is the complaint, that suffices to refuse the order.\r\n"
                "  This situation was different, so I could not just refuse.\r\n"
                "  My question was an instinctive delaying tactic intended to give me a few more seconds to assess the situation.\r\n"
                "  So there.\r\n"
                "  Now, you know the rest of the story.\r\n"
        
            ) ;
        
            storeReplyF( tinP , ifcIDfORMhTTPrEPLY_BIGhEAD , T("/header/idea/danger.html") , 0 , ifcIDsNIPpREDEFINED_HTTPoKtEXThTML , T("Police Story") , T("<B>IdeaFarm</B> (tm) <B>Operations</B> is dangerous work!") , T("IdeaFarm " "(tm) Operations is dangerous work!") , T("Don't just smile.  Lift a finger!") , T("") , T("") , 0 , t1 ) ;
